, delivery dates or service information. Ultimately, this role\u2019s duties and responsibilities are to ensure that the front desk welcomes guests positively and executes all administrative tasks for the TSG office to the highest quality standards to ensure internal and external customer satisfaction. Required Learning Grade 12 At least 2 years front office and receptionist experience as well as office support Office Administration Key Job Outputs Excellent Customer Service for both internal and external customers Assist TSG Management Team with their requirements locally/overseas as they relate to administrative issues Provide accurate information regarding products or services of the company Answer inquiries regarding services and availability of the personnel Schedule, reschedule and cancel appointments when required Maintain meeting room bookings Respond to emails and office correspondence Perform basic record keeping and filing duties Taking minutes of meetings, typing and distributing meeting minutes Receptionist Answer telephone calls and transfer calls to the appropriate person Maintaining an updated contact list for all TSG staff Greet clients, visitors and guests as they enter the office Provide information to callers over the telephone Maintain updated employee attendance and visitors\u2019 records Assist visitors and contractors in filling out forms Provide basic and accurate information in person and via phone or email General administrative work needed as a receptionist at the TSG Johannesburg branch Office Management Report maintenance issues and assist in resolving these issues with relevant staff and contractors Assist in resolving client\u2019s issues and complaints relating to maintenance issues Keep office areas clean and tidy and ensure that staff maintain a clean office Manage inventory of office supplies and refreshments Order office supplies when required Liaise between departments as to their requirements and monitor usage thereof Maintain office security by ensuring the implementation of the relevant security procedures Issuing visitors badges and staff access cards Direct visitors to the appropriate person and office or meeting room Escalate unresolved queries timeously and efficiently to the relevant persons Adhere to ISO procedures and SOPs Core Competencies Integrity: ability to reflect acceptable levels of moral values and business ethics; Customer focus: willingness to respond to the needs of internal and external customers; Result driven: willingness to working well or for surpassing a standard of excellence; Teamwork: willingness to build and maintain a harmonious working environment both internally and externally. Assertiveness: Getting team to perform their tasks without arousing hostility. Business Acumen: the ability to identify business opportunities and successfully manage commercial risks. Financial interpretation: Analyse and understand financial data. Negotiation: Ability to confer or bargain to reach an agreement. Accountability: The obligation to account for one\u2019s activities, accept responsibility for them, and to disclose results in a transparent manner Enquiries / Applications Email your CV to beverleys@ascendismedical.com Closing date of applications will be 30th June 2020 Should you not have received any feedback from the HR Department within 14 days of your submission, please consider your application to be unsuccessful. Apply Now South Africa United StatesCanada ArgentinaAustraliaBelgiÃ«BrasilDeutschlandEspaÃ±aFranceIndiaIrelandItaliaMÃ©xicoNederlandÃsterreichPortugalSchweizSouth AfricaSverigeUnited KingdomÐ Ð¾ÑÑÐ¸Ñíêµ­ä¸­å½æ¥æ¬ Â© 2020 SH Inc. | Privacy | TermsÂ |Â Privacy Center"
